I'm using TeXworks to recognize symbols in my code (ticks and crosses) and have been able to do so by adding the code below to the preamble. 

    \usepackage[utf8]{inputenc}
    \usepackage{amsfonts}
    \usepackage{newunicodechar}
    \newunicodechar{✓}{\checkmark}
    \newunicodechar{×}{$\times$}

When doing this all inside of TeXworks it all turns out nicely. The problem comes when I try to get the same result when doing it all through sphinx. Adding the above code to the preamble in the conf.py file then using `make latexpdf` throws up the following error:

Exception occurred:
  File "/Library/Python/2.7/site-packages/Sphinx-1.1.3-py2.7.egg/sphinx/writers/latex.py", line 266, in astext
